fields.name: Gardens by the Bay
fields.address: 18 Marina Gardens Drive, Singapore 018953, Singapore
fields.review_summary: It is a must visit place in Singapore. the domes were beautiful, we did them at night and they were beautiful and cool, The light show was really good as was the walk amongst the tree tops. We really enjoyed our time walking around the place. you can visit the flower dome and cloud forest at same time. Beautiful walk in the gardens.

fields.name: Singapore Zoo
fields.address: 80 Mandai Lake Road, Singapore 729826, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Kids will have a great time. I visit Singapore a lot, and I always make time for a visit to the zoo. our first visit to singapore zoo. We were able to see animals that are not in US zoos. The place is non-aircon, and the walk will be hot.

fields.name: Singapore Botanic Gardens
fields.address: 1 Cluny Road, Singapore 259569, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Nice walk around, orchids were beautiful and the rainforest walk was good Great gardens. I walked around here and there, and went to orchid garden too. Especially the orchid garden. Great place to have a lovely walk. If you are in Singapore it is a must to visit the orchid garden!

fields.name: Singapore Mass Rapid Transit (SMRT)
fields.address: Singapore 069112, Singapore
fields.review_summary: The stations and trains are very clean. The stations are everywhere. It's clean, clean, clean. So easy to get around Singapore. I can almost go everywhere in Singapore with MRT.

fields.name: Singapore Flyer
fields.address: 30 Raffles Avenue, Singapore 039803, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Flyer is a 45min ride. Everyone might think it's just a ride in a big wheel, yes it's a wheel ride but with an amazing view, you can see almost every place of the city. You really do get the whole view of Singapore from the Singapore Flyer. If you want to see the best of Singapore this the way. Great views across the whole city, very enjoyable.

fields.name: Marina Bay Sands Skypark
fields.address: Bayfront Avenue, 10 | Marina Bay Sands Hotel, Singapore 018956, Singapore
fields.review_summary: I mentioned in my Marina Bay Sands hotel review that staying at this hotel is not cheap but the main reason anyone who would stay at this hotel is for the hotels skypark and infinity pool. The view from the top deck of the marina bay sands is amazing and we'll worth the money to get to the top The view from the top was phenomenal! Great views of the city from the 56th Floor, especially at night. Friendly staff great location near the bay gardens and the casino We booked (and pre-paid) for an inter-connecting room to be told on arrival (following a ridiculously long wait to check in!) What a view of Singapore!

fields.name: National Orchid Garden
fields.address: 1 Cluny Rd | Within the Singapore Botanic Gardens, Singapore 259569, Singapore
fields.review_summary: If you like flowers you will love this place. You will be amazed by the beauty and variety of the orchids on display. Beautiful orchid garden, well worth the visit. A must see at the Botanical Gardens. If you like orchids and beautiful gardens, then this is for you.

fields.name: Marina Bay
fields.address: Marina Boulevard, Singapore 018980, Singapore
fields.review_summary: The night view is great. A great place to view and take in Singapore. Marina Bay Sand 2. Beautiful area, also to walk. Beautiful place Good area to stroll in with a lot of shops to look into.

fields.name: Orchard Road
fields.address: Singapore, Singapore
fields.review_summary: There are a lot of stores along the street. Lots of malls and shops on the street. As always in Singapore, good food! You only go to orchard road if you like shopping! If you like to shop it is a great place to visit.

fields.name: Merlion Park
fields.address: 1 Fullerton Road One Fullerton | Merlion Park, Singapore 049213, Singapore
fields.review_summary: At night though, there were very few people about and we got great pictures. If you have been go to singapore but you didn't visit merlion you will be said that you never been go to singapore. You have to go to Merlion Park if you are in Singapore. One of Singapores many landmarks this was a fun icon to see and it also has great views of Marina Bay Sands and the harbour front area, its a nice walk over the bridge to see the Merlion. This is a must see place in Singapore.

fields.name: Buddha Tooth Relic Temple and Museum
fields.address: 288 South Bridge Road, Singapore 058840, Singapore
fields.review_summary: The tooth relic on the 4th floor is amazing and there is a garden on the fifth floor with a huge praying wheel and 10,000 Buddhas. It is one of the beautiful temples of Buddha. it's a second time i've visited Buddha Tooth Relic temple, this temple is very nice, location near chinatown complex. Value place need to visit. Very different from other temples I have visited.

fields.name: Jurong Bird Park
fields.address: 2 Jurong Hill Jurong Bird Park, Singapore 628925, Singapore
fields.review_summary: good place to visit when you are with kids. there are places that you can feed the birds as well. If its not here,  its probably not a bird. I visited Jurong bird park on 23.04.2017. There is 2 birds show that you must see.

fields.name: Singapore Cable Car
fields.address: 109 Mount Faber Road Faber Peak, Singapore 099203, Singapore
fields.review_summary: If you are riding the cable car, you are likely going to Sentosa Island. Worth enjoying during Singapore visit. Great view on Singapore and Sentosa. Overall, we enjoyed the ride and this is definitely a must go to ride at least once, if you visit Singapore or Sentosa island. Best way to be in Sentosa Island!!

fields.name: Little India
fields.address: Serangoon Road, Singapore, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Must visit while in Singapore even for indians. Very much Indian place, with lots of people and restaurants, temples. Many Indian shops and restaurants. Anyone in Singapore should visit Little India. This is place is for Indians.

fields.name: Clarke Quay
fields.address: 3 River Valley Road Clarke Quay, Singapore 179019, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Lots of great places to eat with also choices to watch live music, shopping, boat rides down the river or simply walk around and take in the atmosphere. There are a lot of places to have a drink and eat, this is a must when visiting Singapore. This is one of the most happening places in town..with so many cafes restaurants bars round the Singapore river.. One can definitely enjoy the Evening over here.. You definitely can not miss this place while your Singapore trip.. Lots n lots of options for food n drinks.. Music night life entertainment.. Beautiful Clarke.. good place for out dating..good for night life..ferry ride is also good..most visit place if u r visiting singapore first time..there is also many night clubs for dance n all too. Clarke Quay is another one of the must see places in Singapore. Many bars and restaurants along the river.

fields.name: Maxwell Food Centre
fields.address: 1 Kadayanallur St, Singapore 069184, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Many stalls with really good food. Well worth the visit to see where the Singapore local will go for a cheap meal. Food is as good as it can be for hawker centre. On the whole, it is a good place to visit. It's a well known food centre for tasty and huge variety of local Hawker food in Singapore and it's very famous for Tian Tian Hainanese Chicken Rice which most people say that it's the fragrant and tasty Rice that makes them to come back for more really it's awesome one must visit this place during their visit to Singapore.

fields.name: The Helix Bridge
fields.address: Linking between Marina Bay and Marina Centre, Singapore 038981, Singapore
fields.review_summary: It is a nice walk across as you get some really good views across the bay, and you can get some really good photos. The Helix Bridge is a structure with a shape of DNA helix, hence the helix bridge. Great views. View around here is good you will see the Marina Bay view. During the night, the lights comes on from the bridge.

fields.name: Mustafa Centre
fields.address: 145 Syed Alwi Road Mustafa Centre, Singapore 207704, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Maybe it was good prices for Singapore though. Whatever you need, you will most probably find it in Mustafa. mustafa centre got everything for your shopping. If you are going to Singapore and trying to find some oleh-oleh then Mustafa if a place you must visit! Its a 24 hour shopping mall with everything you need, I mean everything.

fields.name: National Museum of Singapore
fields.address: 93 Stamford Road, Singapore 178897, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Wonderful building, impressive exhibitions, the museum is worth a visit to understand the history and culture of Singapore. Great building and very interesting displays. This was my second visit to the National Museum of Singapore. For anyone interested in the history of Singapore, a visit to the museum is a must. Great history and interesting exhibits.

fields.name: The Changi Museum
fields.address: 1000 Upper Changi Road North, Singapore 507707, Singapore
fields.review_summary: The story of the war in the Asia/Pacific is not well known enough. The Changi museum and chapel we used the audio guide was informative and interesting. Get to know the history of Singapore at this museum. In saying that, if you're interested in the WWII history and that of the Changi prison, then it's definitely worth a visit. The Changi Museum is well worth a visit.

fields.name: Asian Civilisations Museum
fields.address: 1 Empress Place Empress Place Building, Singapore 179555, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Also it is one of the few free places in Singapore. If you're into Asian artifacts, this is the place. If this is your first time to Singapore then you have to see this museum to appreciate the history. The museum overall has some very interesting exhibits. One of the best museums I have ever visited.

fields.name: River Safari
fields.address: 80 Mandai Lake Road Singapore Zoological Gardens, Singapore 729826, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Can see a few singapore zoo animals too. If you only have time for one, do the zoo. The river safari is right between the Singapore Zoo and Night Zoo. But the highlight for me was the red pandas and the giant pandas. The boat ride on the river goes for 15mins with nothing to see.

fields.name: Arab Street
fields.address: 48 Arab Street Shophouse the Social Hostel, Singapore 199745, Singapore
fields.review_summary: We always visit Arab Street when in Singapore. You can also go to the mosques in that area. But then again, nothing you might not get elsewhere in Singapore. must visit place when you are in Singapore. Lots of shops and restaurants.

fields.name: MacRitchie Nature Trail
fields.address: MacRitchie Reservoir Park, Singapore 298717, Singapore
fields.review_summary: This is one of the few nature trails in Singapore, and if you're up for hiking and nature, or if you just want to get away from the city, you should definitely visit MacRitchie. Like anywhere in Singapore you want to take water. Treetop walk was worth doing but make sure you walk the right way around as it is a one-way only walk across the treetop bridge. Bring lots of water, but don't even THINK about feeding the monkeys. I certainly did - walked the 10km trail.

fields.name: Singapore River
fields.address: Boat, Clarke, Robertson Quays, Singapore, Singapore
fields.review_summary: A great relaxing walk along the Singapore River, with restaurants, bars and shopping. Great for walking or boat tours. SIngapore is great place for walking. There are boat cruises across the river. Following the river further is Boat Quay, Clarke Quay and Robertson Quay.

fields.name: Raffles Hotel Arcade
fields.address: 1 Beach Road Raffles Hotel, Singapore 189673, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Yes the Singapore Slings are expensive, but as long as you go in expecting this, you are more likely to enjoy yourself. Visit the Long Bar for a Singapore Sling. A cool experience with good drinks and great atmosphere. I always visit Raffles Hotel when I stay in Singapore. There are several shops around the hotel and a gift shop.

fields.name: Lau Pa Sat Festival Pavilion
fields.address: 18 Raffles Quay Telok Ayer Festival Market, Singapore 048582, Singapore
fields.review_summary: So its really more of the place than anything else. You know its good when the local eat there. Many food stalls, you just has to try it yourself. Enjoy, ,,.,7,,,.There were so many foods and it's the place to eat satay. But I didn't know which stall these satay were from.

fields.name: Battlebox
fields.address: 2 Cox Terrace | Fort Canning Park, Singapore 179622, Singapore
fields.review_summary: I would definitely recommend a visit, especially if you're interested in history! The guided tour is very informative as our guide is very knowledgeable. The fall of Singapore to the Japanese in WW2. A very good tour with an excellent tour guide. Tour guide was very informative, goes for about 1 hour, well worth it, very interesting on how the British surrendered Singapore to the Japanese in 1945.

fields.name: Peranakan Museum
fields.address: 39 Armenian Street, Singapore 179941, Singapore
fields.review_summary: The exhibits and displays are beautiful and well-designed. I learned so much about the Peranakan culture and Singapore. The Peranakan Museum does that. The building itself is just beautiful, and houses displays of the Peranakan people's culture, art, and every day life objects. If you want to know Singapore must visit this Museum.

fields.name: Vivo City
fields.address: 1 Harbourfront Walk Vivo City, Singapore 098585, Singapore
fields.review_summary: All in one shopping mall 3. Food court in Vivo was quite big and has lots of local food. It is just across Sentosa Island. A good place to shop though. Whatever you need, you will find it at Vivo City!

fields.name: East Coast Park
fields.address: Along East Coast Parkway and East Coast Park Service Road, Singapore 455486, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Good place to cycle and enjoy the beach. It's ok for a walk every once in a while, but this is Singapore, so there are no beaches. A great day out and a great place to relax. Lots of people will be enjoying their time during weekends. And East Coast Park is not one of them.

fields.name: ArtScience Museum at Marina Bay Sands
fields.address: 10 Bayfront Avenue Marina Bay Sands, Singapore 018956, Singapore
fields.review_summary: It was one of our best days out while in Singapore and this is a place not to miss if you have kids under 14 years of age. The Building is great,  the Design very good ! The future world exhibit was good and very interactive. The museum is an exhibition in itself. We visited two exhibitions in the museum.

fields.name: Kranji War Memorial
fields.address: 9 Woodlands Road, Singapore 738656, Singapore
fields.review_summary: This is a must do when in Singapore. This was my third visit to the memorial. Didn't know this memorial was here but a peaceful place to visit. Kranji War Memorial perhaps is not on everyone's list of places to visit when it comes to Singapore. About a 15 minute walk from the Kranji MRT, but worth the time.

fields.name: The Southern Ridges
fields.address: Alexandra Road | Mount Faber Park; Telok Blangah Hill Park; or Kent Ridge Park, Singapore 099203, Singapore
fields.review_summary: We started the walk at Kent Ridge Park. Singapore's best views along the waY. I walked from start to the end of it, which is to be the Henderson Bridge (wave-like bridge). Nice walk with some good views across the city. to Hort Park.

fields.name: National Gallery Singapore
fields.address: 1 St. Andrew's Road #01-01 National Gallery Singapore, Singapore 178957, Singapore
fields.review_summary: One of the best exhibitions I have seen. This new Singapore National Gallery is really well done. If there is one place to see in Singapore, this is it!. A must see for the buildings' history and architecture as the former Supreme Court and City Hall and their use as an art gallery within. Where is the art in the gallery?

fields.name: Sri Mariamman Temple
fields.address: 244 South Bridge Road Sri Mariamman Temple, Singapore 058793, Singapore
fields.review_summary: You need of course to take your shoes off to get in. This Hindu Temple is a must see in Chinatown. It was good experience for non Hindu tourists. This is a beautiful Hindu temple in Chinatown, very interesting place. Visit the temple.

fields.name: Fort Canning Park
fields.address: River Valley Rd, Singapore 179038, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Great place to go if you like parks & history. A walk into Singapore's history. it was a really nice Park to walk around, Fort Canning was really interesting to look at, lovely kept Garden and Lawn and well worth a look, if you looking for something different to do. We walked through this park and it was nice to visit. You can walk around or over Fort Canning hill.

fields.name: ION Orchard
fields.address: 2 Orchard Turn, Singapore 238801, Singapore
fields.review_summary: We only went to the one in the food court. The shops in this mall are great. the main reason why i love visiting singapore is all city are well connected via anything. all brands, that you can think of, are in this mall. There are many other malls along Orchard Rd too!

fields.name: Sultan Mosque
fields.address: 3 Muscat Street Masjid Sultan, Singapore 198833, Singapore
fields.review_summary: We'll find all Muslim in Singapore here. Non-Muslims are allowed inside the building, but not inside the main prayer hall. A very nice Mosque in the Arab Street of Singapore. I went to this mosque many times during my visit to Singapore.

fields.name: Chinatown Heritage Centre
fields.address: 48 Pagoda Street, Singapore 059207, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Very well priced and a must visit for anyone who enjoys the history of the place they re visiting We were recommended this museum by the guide on our walking tour. Overall, a most interesting museum. This is a museum showing and display the history of Chinese Migrants to Singapore and the development of China Town in early stages.it is interesting and worth to visit. A visit to the Chinatown heritage museum is a must. Some of the exhibits were interesting and showed how the migrants lived in cramped spaces!

fields.name: Haw Par Villa
fields.address: 262 Pasir Panjang Road | 1-min walk from Haw Par Villa MRT Station, Singapore 118628, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Hardly I see anyone visiting this place. During old time, whoever who visits Singapore must visit Haw Par Villa as well! Haw Par Villa, also known as the Tiger Balm Gardens, is a tourist attraction that seems out-of-this-world. :D It's different and worth the visit if you like statues. I have never seen another theme park like this.

fields.name: Science Centre Singapore
fields.address: 15 Science Centre Road Singapore Science Centre, Singapore 609081, Singapore
fields.review_summary: initially i thought of cool stuffs and latest gadgets to be found there but it was lame things and people were crowding at macdonalds rather than visiting the place... lol I give four start because I find that ticket some expensive and actually more of the activities was given for children. There is too much to do on one visit, which is always good. Very good place for kids and adults who like science. We visited the Singapore science center in December'13. There are lots of exhibits to see and play with, every time we visit there seems to be something new to see or do.

fields.name: Chinese and Japanese Gardens
fields.address: 1 Chinese Garden Road Chinese Garden, Singapore 619795, Singapore
fields.review_summary: The Japanese gardens were open on our visit and very tranquil, as were the Chinese gardens and its Pagoda. Nice visit if you like parks. During our visit there appeared to be more gardeners than visitors, but certainly worth a visit if visiting Singapore. then walk around 7mins from the MRT to the garden. The gardens are really a nice place to visit.

fields.name: Takashimaya Singapore
fields.address: 391 Orchard Road Ngee Ann City Tower a, Singapore 238873, Singapore

fields.name: Marina Barrage
fields.address: 8 Marina Gardens Drive Marina Barrage, Singapore 018951, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Its only reservoir building but nice architecture.. Verry interesting with grass on top.... U can walk from garden bays.. its near maybe just 1 km.... Take a way in side of garden building.. and u will found it.. Visit this place if you have an interest in engineering projects, particularly water related ones, or if you just want to enjoy great views of the Singapore city skyline. on the barrage, Great place for family picnic and kite flying. Great place for picnic.

fields.name: F1 - Singapore Grand Prix
fields.address: Marina Bay Street Circuit, Singapore 038975, Singapore
fields.review_summary: We attended all three days and had an amazing time. It was 3 days of great racing, food and entertainment. And of course the race! Well done Singapore.

fields.name: Chijmes
fields.address: 30 Victoria Street Chijmes, Singapore 187996, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Went to CHIJMES for a drink at one of the bars. Great complex, beautiful church looks lovely in the evening. Lots of great bars and restaurants here, in a good location. One of the best place to eat, drink and visit.

fields.name: National Library of Singapore
fields.address: 100 Victoria Street National Library Building, Singapore 188064, Singapore
fields.review_summary: I think it has 13 floors? There are National Libraries all over Singapore so you can definitely be sure that you will have one near you. Loved there information section, and visit every time when we visit. These places are for people to borrow books or read books there.

fields.name: The Intan
fields.address: 69 Joo Chiat Terrace, Singapore 427231, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Alvin, the owner of the Intan Museum was friendly too! It's not just a museum, it's an experience. Definitely will ask my friend visit The Intan. A must visit in Singapore for anyone interested in heritage & this unique culture.

fields.name: Singapore Art Museum
fields.address: 71 Bras Basah Road Singapore Art Museum, Singapore, Singapore
fields.review_summary: The building itself is worth a visit as it was an old colonial building. Great art pieces were displayed. If you're looking for something to do in Singapore, I would tell you to look a little more. This is the best art museum I have ever visited! At the time of our visit, there was an excellent exhibition on called 'After Utopia' featuring contemporary Asian artists.

fields.name: Fountain of Wealth
fields.address: 3 Temasek Boulevard Suntec City Mall | Suntec City Mall, Singapore 038983, Singapore
fields.review_summary: It s a good place to take a photo at any time of the day or night and inside the mall itself is a great place for many different types of food. The Fountain of Wealth is just that - a fountain. This might have been the timing, though.

fields.name: Singapore Visitor Centre
fields.address: 216 Orchard Road | Orchard Gateway @ Emerald, Opposite Somerset MRT, Singapore 238898, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Very helpful staff. she even gave many suggestions on what to-do etc.. tourists are able to select what the places of interest based on the recommendations and print the itinerary using the system provided. There is always something new to see and the staff at the Visitor Centre have the information and the maps available.

fields.name: Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve
fields.address: 301 Neo Tiew Crescent, Singapore 718925, Singapore
fields.review_summary: One of the last wetland reserves in Singapore. ), see how Singapore used to look. It will take around 2 hours to walk around the wetland reserve. Saw mudskippers, monitor lizards and and lots of different birds. Good place to do some birding or immerse in some nature time.

fields.name: Esplanade Park
fields.address: Connaught Drive, Singapore, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Come at night and you'll find yourself in a great place for a walk, taking pictures, and enjoy the surroundings with nice city lights. A must see place in Singapore.

fields.name: Lucky Plaza
fields.address: 304 Orchard Road Lucky Plaza, Singapore 238863, Singapore
fields.review_summary: As for buying stuff at this mall I didn't see anything that worth mentioning (except of buying Sim cards for tourist the $15 one for 5 days from Singtel can be found there). the price is over. Compare to other places in Orchard area, i think Lucky Plaza is the most cheaper place to shop souvenir such as chocolate, t-shirt and other souvenir with Singapore logo..you can find the 2 foodcourt inside with arround $3-$7, you can take a lunch here. And some Singapore Souvenir shop. Never to buy at Lucky Plaza again, 'specially from this shop...

fields.name: Raffles City
fields.address: 252 North Bridge Rd, Singapore 179101, Singapore
fields.review_summary: If you are in the area then it is a good one to visit (and as it is opposite Raffles Hotel then I guess a lot of people will find themselves in the area) but i would not say it is worth travelling far to, as there are lots of other good Mall's in Singapore Awesome place for conventions and events. Big shopping mall with department store, food court, supermarket, MRT accessible but it's the City Hall station, not the Raffles Station, the food hall is great with small shops for dinning in a budget. A great shopping centre in the centre of the city.

fields.name: Sri Veeramakaliamman Temple
fields.address: 141 Serangoon Road, Singapore 218042, Singapore
fields.review_summary: If you are in Singapore then it is a must that you visit some of its many temples, and this one is beautiful. This is the best Hindu temple to which I've been. Worth visiting this temple in Singapore Near Little India Area It is bit crowded, but still a nice one Great temple!

fields.name: Resort World Sentosa Casino
fields.address: 8 Sentosa Gateway Resorts World Sentosa, Singapore 098269, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Amazing this is entry to non singapore passport is free and if singapore passport then its 100 SGD. And also besides gambling, there're a lot of attraction in Sentosa that you can do, so it's worth it spending time here. Good casino inside Sentosa resort world.

fields.name: Kampong Glam
fields.address: Kampong Glam, Singapore, Singapore
fields.review_summary: A must for everyone who visits Singapore. Others not, so we shopped there. I visited Kampong Glam twice.

fields.name: St Andrew's Cathedral
fields.address: 11 St. Andrew's Road St. Andrew's Cathedral, Singapore 178959, Singapore
fields.review_summary: This is hardly a cathedral and better from the outside. It is Singapore's first Anglican church. From outside, the cathedral is very beautiful.

fields.name: Holland Village
fields.address: Holland Avenue Lorong Liput, Lorong Mambong,, Singapore 278967, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Lots of western style restaurants, bars, shops and very lively. Now I can say I've been to Holland Village. Great place for eating and drinking.

fields.name: Emerald Hill
fields.address: Off Orchard Road, Singapore, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Worth the stop to check it out A nostalgic place that is full of peranakan influence, a nice one hour walk to feel a different part of this vibrant city After a stroll along Orchard Road I turned into Emerald Hill road and after walking past a couple of bars and restaurants the road is lined with beautiful restored terrace houses. The Emerald Hill Road is worth to see,  if you like nice old Buildings.

fields.name: Wild Wild Wet
fields.address: 1 Pasir Ris Close E!Hub@Downtown East, Singapore 519599, Singapore
fields.review_summary: My children have so much fun, they said it was the best day. The slides at this place were good. Overall a great fun time for my kids and myself.....will definitely come again for sure! The crowds were small and there was zero waiting time for the rides which were open. But I will return again :) My friends and I have visited the water slide park in Sentosa several times and eventually made the trip out to Wild Wild Wet to see how it compares.

fields.name: Plaza Singapura
fields.address: 68 Orchard Road, Singapore 238839, Singapore
fields.review_summary: It's probably more of a mall for the locals, having stores such as Spotlight and a huge Daiso (Japanese $2 shop), sports stores, toy stores etc. This mall is one of the first mall in Singapore. The mall had all the shops we could want.

fields.name: Thian Hock Keng Temple
fields.address: 158 Telok Ayer Street | Chinatown, Singapore 068613, Singapore
fields.review_summary: If you are into temples, please visit this place. You may have seen temples like this one.

fields.name: Mint Museum of Toys
fields.address: 26 Seah Street, Singapore 188382, Singapore
fields.review_summary: There are a lot of toys collection. I'm not even sure of they are old or new or if they should be in the/a museum. There is a small museum shop near the entrance, which sells some nice and reasonably priced collectible tin toys.

fields.name: Singapore Philatelic Museum
fields.address: 23B Coleman Street Singapore Philatelic Museum, Singapore 179807, Singapore
fields.review_summary: On my visit to Singapore this time, I visited the Singapore Philatelic Museum. One can also buy stamps for collection.... if you like to collect stamps.... A nicely presented little museum on stamps. This place will appeal to stamp and non-stamp lovers, a small museum of 2 storeys houses 6 rooms and others: 1) Orange Room - level 1 - Facts about stamps and stamp displays 2) Purple Room - Level 1 - Singapore stamp history and stamp displays 3) Lee Foundation Atrium - Level 1 - Currently showing the old postcards of Singapore 4) Room of Rarities - Level 2 - Old stamps of Singapore and Straits Settlements display 5) Heritage Room - Level 2 - Costumes of Colonial Singapore, Musical Instruments, Cultural Festivals, and traditional trades 6) Special Exhibits Room - Level 2 - Currently showing snake facts and related stamp displays 7) Collection of miniature postboxes of the UK, China, Spain, Portugal, Hong Kong, Macau, USA, Japan and Singapore - Level 2 8) Spices Display - Level 2 - Currently showing spices cultivation map of Old Singapore.

fields.name: Cavenagh Bridge
fields.address: Mouth of Singapore River, Singapore, Singapore
fields.review_summary: The night views from the other side, as well as when on the bridge, are beautiful and if with a partner or loved one, then make for a memorable romantic evening too! This bridge is one Singapore river.

fields.name: City Square Mall
fields.address: 180 Kitchener Road City Square Mall, Singapore 208539, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Very nice mall in Little India, Singapore. There are lots of places to shop. This shopping mall has almost everything you need.

fields.name: Bukit Brown Cemetery
fields.address: Lorong Halwa, Singapore, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Be sure to go with someone who knows Singapore history. Beautiful trees, very interesting graves. It's not that there are more Bukit Browns around Singapore.

fields.name: Marina Square
fields.address: 6 Raffles Boulevard Marina Square, Singapore 039594, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Surrounded by hotels such as the Mandarin OrientalBur for and Pan Pacific, Marina Square gives you access to and from Suntec City, Citylink Mall, Millenia Walk and the Esplanade theatres on the bay. There are many shops and many exits/entrances.

fields.name: Statue of Raffles
fields.address: Downtown Core, Singapore, Singapore
fields.review_summary: It's a statue. A nice place to see the Boat Quay, Raffles is an institution in Singapore and you cant go by much without seeing the name.

fields.name: The Pinnacle @ Duxton
fields.address: 1 Cantonment Road The Pinnacle @ Duxton, Singapore 080001, Singapore
fields.review_summary: It's gives an amazing 360 degree view of Singapore without the crowds of tourists or high prices. Go to building G to find little office to pay the $5 to get access to the 50th floor. anything else to do there, well, nothing... 360 view of Singapore with just 5SingD!

fields.name: Katong District
fields.address: East Coast Road, Singapore, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Katong is the place to be. If you are looking for place to eat an inexpensive meal, and have quality food, then Katong is the place to come.

fields.name: Surviving the Japanese Occupation: War and Its Legacies
fields.address: 351 Upper Bukit Timah Road, Singapore 588192, Singapore

fields.name: Robertson Quay
fields.address: Near Singapore River, Singapore, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Also nice just for an evening stroll without drinks or dining. Great area by the river for walking with lots of nice eating places and wine bars.

fields.name: Suntec Singapore Convention & Exhibition Centre
fields.address: 1 Raffles Boulevard Singapore Int'l Convention & Exhibition Ctr, Singapore 039593, Singapore
fields.review_summary: I would say very huge shopping center and many shops and hotels available. If you happen to have a conference here, check out the other floors.

fields.name: IMM Outlet Mall
fields.address: 2 Jurong East Street 21, Singapore 609601, Singapore
fields.review_summary: It's outlet shopping. But if you are looking for high-end shopping, IMM is not the place.

fields.name: Tiger Brewery
fields.address: 459 Jalan Ahmad Ibrahim, Singapore 639934, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Sorry folks- if you are looking for a brewery tour go elsewhere. We found the transport easy via MRT and bus (but we have travelled to Singapore many times).

fields.name: Red Dot Design Museum
fields.address: 11 Marina Boulevard, Singapore 018940, Singapore
fields.review_summary: The Red Dot Design Museum is definitely a place to visit when in Singapore. And of course, there are a lot of great things in the gift shop!

fields.name: Labrador Nature Reserve
fields.address: Labrador Villa Road Tanjong Berlayer Park, Singapore 119187, Singapore
fields.review_summary: The park has a small hill and hence it's advisable that first hill is explored and then ascend downhill to enjoy a beautiful view of the sea. so it was a great place to walk while visiting the city. There is also a small and old harbour where you can walk out to, to enjoy the cool sea breeze.

fields.name: Singapore Cricket Club
fields.address: A Connaught Drive Singapore Cricket Club, Singapore 179681, Singapore
fields.review_summary: The veranda serves some of the best curries in Singapore whilst you look over the Padang and watch the tennis,  Cricket, rugby, Hockey or lawn bowls. If you haven't been to the Singapore Cricket Club, you must.

fields.name: Tekka Centre
fields.address: 665 Buffalo Road Zhujiao Centre (Tekka Market) 210665 Singapore, Singapore 210665, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Mostly indian foods are available. Good access from the little India MRT.

fields.name: Singapore Turf Club
fields.address: 1 Turf Club Avenue Singapore Racecourse | Singapore Racecourse, Singapore 738078, Singapore
fields.review_summary: There is always someone there to help with how the locals bet. This is the only horse racing track in Singapore. Easy train ride on mrt cost 2.50 then 6$ to get into the track, you could sit an watch the horses come out, then walk across into the air condition stand to watch the races, food and drink hall on same level, great day.

fields.name: Kuan Yin Thong Hood Cho Temple
fields.address: 178 Waterloo Street Kwan im Temple, Singapore 187964, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Otherwise, it is a good place to see how the locals make their offerings Came upon this temple while strolling in the Bugis area. This temple I think was one of the best temples I have seen so far.

fields.name: Bollywood Veggies
fields.address: 100 Neo Tiew Road, Singapore 719026, Singapore
fields.review_summary: I loved it and would go again every time I visit Singapore. The plants are well-labelled, so it was easy for the kids to learn about the different plants and trees there. If you wish to visit different off the track of Singapore then you should try this place.

fields.name: Parkview Square
fields.address: 600 North Bridge Road Parkview Square, Singapore 188778, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Art Deco building looks like something out of a Batman movie and Wine Fairies 'fly' up on a wire to get your wine bottle! The building is in Art Deco style and the inside is amazing, really beautiful.

fields.name: Jurong East Swimming Complex
fields.address: 21 Jurong East Street 31, Singapore 609517, Singapore
fields.review_summary: What a...More Reach at Chinese Garden MRT, walk 500 meters to this place, Full of water everywhere, Lazy River, Wave Pool, Swimming pool, Three Water rides and couple of baby and toddler pools. One of the the best places in singapore where you can take your children and spend time with full of enjoyment the whole day You get down in Chineese garden MRT in green line and cross the road near the signal..You will find this fantastin swimming complex For entrance of $2,you can use MRT card itself or buy ticket in the counter Do not forget to take children and swimming dress is must to wear Cheap.

fields.name: Lee Kong Chian Natural History Museum
fields.address: 2 Conservatory Drive | National University of Singapore, Singapore 117377, Singapore
fields.review_summary: While Lee Kong Chian Natural History Museum is a lot smaller than other museums in Australia, etc, it still allows visitors to amuse themselves for a good 3-4 hours, and this is the first natural history museum in Singapore. This is an interesting visit worth about 1.5 hours of your time. Overall, the Lee Kong Chian Natural History Museum would be somewhere where I, as a local, would take a friend from a foreign country to visit, especially for someone who is interested in the flora and fauna of the region, or someone who wants to visit somewhere more 'unique' and off the beaten tourist track.

fields.name: National Stadium
fields.address: 2 Stadium Walk, Singapore 397718, Singapore
fields.review_summary: The stadium is not just for sport event, it is also for many others. There's just no need unless it's your first stadium.

fields.name: Central Business District
fields.address: Shenton Way, Singapore, Singapore
fields.review_summary: This is the modern area south of the Singapore River that consists of many modern high rise buildings as is you might expect quite impressive.The area is adjacent to the Marina Bay area and raffles Plaza and is worth a visit. The Central Business Disctrict is the business sector of the city in Singapore, nevertheless it is still a great place to go if you want to shop (after Orchard Road), or take a look at Raffles Place or around the city.

fields.name: Great World City Shopping Centre
fields.address: 1 Kim Seng Promenade Great World City, Singapore 237994, Singapore
fields.review_summary: if you have lot of time, then you can visit this place like we did Great shopping mall with everything. Clean, good food court, restaurants, money changer and good variety of shops ranging from jewelry stores, clothing,  electronics,  cold storage ect.

fields.name: Hort Park
fields.address: 33 Hyderabad Road, Singapore 119578, Singapore
fields.review_summary: This was my 2nd visit to Hort park. However, it will be good if you can bring your own food.

fields.name: Sri Srinivasa Perumal Temple
fields.address: 397 Serangoon Road, Singapore 218123, Singapore
fields.review_summary: It feels very nice to visit on any auspicious day and it also feels very good and peaceful as you feel you are very close to divinity On of the most famous Hindu temples in Singapore, as usually full of colours, interesting painting an sculptures.. Nice place, best time to visit is...More We went here on a weekday afternoon, so there were no people around. This definitely was one of the interesting places I visited in Singapore.

fields.name: Pasir Ris Town Park
fields.address: Pasir Ris Road, Singapore, Singapore
fields.review_summary: Access to the park is via the Pasir Ris bus interchange (10 minute walk to Car Park A) or bus 403 from the interchange, to access the park at Pasir Ris Road (nearer the children's playground) Several highlights of the park include cycling tracks and bicycle rental, a pony ride area, a mangrove forest walk, and a large children playground. We like to visit at the weekend, when the park is lively, it's nice to see the local people enjoying the park.

fields.address: 31K Pepys Road, Singapore 118458, Singapore
fields.review_summary: The show is about how Malay Regiment fought the Japanese during WW2 at Bukit Chandu, only a few soldiers survived the battle. Well worth a look, either on a walk from Hort Park or on a visit to Kent Ridge Park.
